&lt;p&gt;Join our team at Core One! Our mission is to be at the forefront of devising analytical, operational and technical solutions to our Nation&#39;s most complex national security challenges. In order to achieve our mission, Core One values people first! We are committed to recruiting, nurturing, and retaining top talent! We offer a competitive total compensation package that sets us apart from our competition. Core One is a team-oriented, dynamic, and growing company that values exceptional performance!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Core One seeks a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Receptionist/ Administrative Assistant &lt;/strong&gt;who will work from the front desk and present a professional and friendly demeanor while greeting staff and guests while ensuring overall efficiency of the office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary Range: $20Hr - $25Hr&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide a high level of customer service over the phone, in person and online while interacting with staff, visitors and customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pick up, drop off, prepare, sort and disperse mail, which may require travel to local USPS, FedEx or UPS facilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check-in and check-out guests including issuance of visitor badges and maintenance of the parking access logs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain all conference rooms including tracking of calendars, preparing meeting spaces by ensuring supplies are stocked and the rooms are tidied between meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the office kitchens including ordering and inventory of all kitchen supplies as well as maintenance of the coffee machines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee and maintain common areas ensuring a clean and welcoming environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage office supply inventory, to include company swag and coordinate with vendors as appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with corporate events, including coordination, setup, execution and breakdown&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with general administrative tasks from other departments as time allows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 1 year experience in an administrative position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to multitask and prioritize items effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility and willingness to help in other departments as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable of working in a team environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpersonal communication skills and computer skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Office 365&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to execute tasks with effective follow up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent business etiquette, work ethics, appearance, verbal and phone communication manners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have own transportation and ability to run general office errands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
